cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SE. 

The paper is primarily focused on efficient data transfer between different database management systems (DBMSs) for data analytics workloads. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of shared-nothing engines, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The tool developed, PipeGen, involves the generation of data pipes, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also evaluates the performance of PipeGen, which falls under the category of cs.DM (Data Mining). Finally, the implementation and evaluation of the prototype involve software engineering principles, which is related to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
